Here's how to implement all three in your `EditProductPage`:

**1 & 2. Intercept back navigation and confirm:**

Override `OnBackButtonPressed` (hardware/gesture back) and hook into Shell's `Navigating` event for the shell back button:

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    protected override void OnAppearing()
    {
        base.OnAppearing();
        Shell.Current.Navigating += OnShellNavigating;
    }

    protected override void OnDisappearing()
    {
        base.OnDisappearing();
        Shell.Current.Navigating -= OnShellNavigating;
    }

    // Intercepts Shell back button / URI navigation
    private async void OnShellNavigating(object sender, ShellNavigatingEventArgs e)
    {
        if (!_hasUnsavedChanges || e.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Push)
            return;

        var deferral = e.GetDeferral();

        bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!leave)
            e.Cancel();

        deferral.Complete();
    }

    // Intercepts Android hardware/gesture back button
    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (!_hasUnsavedChanges)
            return base.OnBackButtonPressed();

        MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(async () =>
        {
            bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (leave)
                await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
        });

        return true; // true = cancel default navigation
    }
}
```

**3. Custom "Cancel" back button:**

In your XAML, hide the default back button and add your own toolbar item:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.EditProductPage"
             Shell.BackButtonBehavior="{StaticResource CancelBackButton}">

    <ContentPage.Resources>
        <BackButtonBehavior x:Key="CancelBackButton"
                            IsVisible="True"
                            TextOverride="Cancel"
                            Command="{Binding CancelCommand}" />
    </ContentPage.Resources>

    <!-- Or inline: -->
    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                            Command="{Binding CancelCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- page content -->
</ContentPage>
```

With the command in your view model (or code-behind):

```csharp
[RelayCommand]
private async Task Cancel()
{
    if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        bool leave = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!leave) return;
    }

    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
}
```

**Key points:**
- **`Shell.Navigating` + deferral** — the only way to asynchronously cancel shell-level navigation.
- **`OnBackButtonPressed`** — needed separately for Android hardware/gesture back (doesn't fire `Shell.Navigating`).
- **`BackButtonBehavior`** with `TextOverride` and `Command` — replaces the arrow with "Cancel" and routes through your confirmation logic, bypassing the default back behavior.
